						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up near the Āñjanēyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Rāmadēva, 1628 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Prabhava, Phālguṇa,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1628 A.D., March.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record also seems to register the gift of the village Turukapalli to <hi rend="italic">jātikarta</hi> Nārāyaṇa. See No. 321 above.</p>						

						</summary>
